  <h2><img src="/images/dvd-rom-big.png" alt="Skeptoid DVD" width="170" height="170" align="right" style="margin-left:15px;">Join Us!</h2>
  <p>Skeptoid is a full-time project and <strong><em><u>depends on</u></em></strong> listener support for its existence.</p>
  <p>As a supporter, you get to be a part of this important work; but more than that, you'll be part of the small team that makes it financially possible. Skeptoid Media, Inc. is a small, independent California nonprofit and works full-time making this material available for free not only to schools, but to everyone, worldwide.</p>
  <p class="inabox" style="width:150px; float:right; margin-left: 15px;">The DVD-ROM includes:<br>
    &#8226; All <em>Skeptoid</em> episodes<br>
    &#8226; An HD version of <em>Here Be Dragons</em><br>
    &#8226; The <em>Here Be Dragons</em> soundtrack by award-winning composer Lee Sanders<br>
    &#8226; HD versions of all <em>inFact</em> video podcast episodes<br>
    &#8226; An HD version of <em>The Secret of the Gypsy Queen</em><br>
    &#8226; Enhanced version of <em>Screwed!</em> (song only)<br>
    &#8226; HD version of <em>The Making of Screwed!</em> video<br>
    &#8226; HD teaser for <em>The Skeptologists</em> TV pilot<br>
    &#8226; A cool Skeptoid sticker! </p>
  <p><a href="/testimonials.php" target="_blank">Read this to see what kind of difference Skeptoid is making to people.</a> </p>
  <p>You may not be aware of all that Skeptoid does:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Skeptoid remains free of commercial content, ads, and lengthy intros and outros that reduce your listening enjoyment.<br>
      <br>
    </li>
    <li>Skeptoid comes to you every Tuesday at 7am Pacific, every week, every month, every year since 2006.<br>
      <br>
    </li>
    <li>Skeptoid is the core foundation around which all of my other skeptical outreach projects (web, TV, and film) are based. Your contribution to Skeptoid helps bring much more than just one podcast to those most in need. </li>
  </ul>
  <p>Please take a moment to join Skeptoid, and be a part of spreading critical thinking and the excitement of knowledge.<br>
    <br>
    <img src="/images/signature.gif" alt="Brian Dunning"><br>
    Brian Dunning<br>
    <br>
  </p>
  <blockquote>
    <p style="text-indent: -30px">PS - To thank you for your help, please let me send you this <u>free autographed DVD-ROM</u> with all the cool extras. It's an easy way to share Skeptoid with those who need  it!<br>
      <br>
    </p>
  </blockquote>
